spaska.data

Class NominalValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • spaska.data.Value
      • spaska.data.NominalValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable<Value>

    public final class NominalValue
extends Value
    Represents a nominal value attribute in the data. Nominal values are just finite list of values that an attribute can have. A simple example is the class attribute that contains the label for an instance.
